The formula is correct. Your assumption as to your current skill level is where the error lies. When you put the first point into a skill, you get it at a skill equal to your current level. You currently have a skill of 16, and will not be able to gain any more skill (by any method) until level 19 when the cap becomes 20 and you can gain 4 more points. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujackylhunter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jackylhunter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(4/11/02 11:01:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=149.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Research Skill?</span><hr size=1> Just a note about the Pet spells in Katta.  They are the mid level pets, I think 39 and up, I'm a 28th level mage, and I only have 3 of my 4 24th level pets now.  <br>
