<br>
    I should probably farm the Sarnak fort in Illomen again just to collect more words and ice, but am more focussed on levelling at the moment.<br>
<br>
    Under normal circumstances I charge 10p to research a pet, assuming you provide a pet scroll from the previous level.  For higher level pets I charge 15p, assuming you provide a pet scroll from the previous level.  If the money is ever a burden, I waive the charge, or simply ask to donate whatever you feel is appropriate.  I'm pretty flexible in that regard.  I also accept donated words and components, if I need to stock up.  The big thing though, is you provide the pet scroll to research with.  I think that's fair enough to ask. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucaleem.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caleem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(4/25/02 10:42:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=149.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Research Skill?</span><hr size=1> I know it's a pain, and I know it's probably cheaper to just use the skill points, but I want to do the practice research route for RP and acomplishment reasons.<br>
