<br>
If you can't buy the spells you need, I would strongly suggest that you still not do reasearch, but that you find some Mage who has a high research to do it for you. <br>
<br>
If you insist on raising spell research yourself, the only viable way is to head to your trainer and pay for increases in spell research until you run out of plat. Then, when you still fail at making that new pet, wait until you get even more plat to pour into training. The practice research is ABSOLUTELY worthless. It's far more difficult to do the &quot;practice&quot; research than it is to attempt to actually make spells. I made lots of copies of Everfount as I was attempting to raise my skill before I came to realize how futile spell research is.<br>
<br>
My advice: save your money, save your time. Buy your spells from a vendor or get a friendly Mage (who, like me, was suckered into waisting their time on spell research) to make it for you. There's no sense in even more young Mages falling victim to poor game design!!<br>
<br>
/rant off... no, not really, I'm still xzsjg'd over this!<br>
